Thanks for reaching out—happy to share. For this hiring cycle, our top priorities for the first 60–90 days are:

1) Ramp fast and deliver a visible win: get fully oriented on our product/workflows, take ownership of a well-scoped project, and ship an improvement that moves a clear metric (quality, cycle time, customer experience, or revenue impact—depending on the team).
2) Build strong cross-functional trust: partner effectively with stakeholders, clarify requirements early, and communicate progress/risks in a predictable way.
3) Improve the system, not just the task: leave behind cleaner processes/docs/tooling so the team is faster after your work lands.

What makes someone stand out for us:
- Evidence of shipping meaningful outcomes quickly (examples with scope, constraints, and measurable results).
- Strong prioritization and problem framing (you can separate “urgent” from “important” and propose a plan).
- Clear written and verbal communication, especially when aligning multiple stakeholders.
- Ownership mindset: you proactively identify gaps, propose solutions, and follow through.

If you’re open to it, tell me (a) what kind of “quick impact” you’re most proud of delivering in a prior role, and (b) what environment helps you do your best work (ambiguity level, collaboration style). That will help me map you to the highest-impact work here.

- Comfort with data/metrics to guide decisions and demonstrate impact.
- Evidence of learning speed—picking up new domains/tools and becoming productive fast.

What success looks like in the first 3–6 months:
- First 30 days: understand our product/processes, build relationships, and take ownership of a scoped project.
- 60–90 days: independently drive a core project to a concrete deliverable with clear success metrics.
- 3–6 months: own a larger area, improve a key metric/process, and be a go-to partner for cross-functional teams.
